<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Section Number="0732.501" xmlns="http://StatRev.xsd"><Catchline xml:space="preserve">Who may make a will.</Catchline><SectionBody><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">Any person who is of sound mind and who is either 18 or more years of age or an emancipated minor may make a will.</Text></SectionBody><History xml:space="preserve">s. 1, ch. 74-106; s. 113, ch. 75-220; s. 41, ch. 2001-226.</History><Note><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">Created from former s. 731.04.</Text></Note></Section>